### ===========================================
### Error Handling Demo — HTTP Tests
###
### Demonstrates ExceptionMapper responses:
###   - ServiceExceptionMapper   → custom business errors (404, 409)
###   - ConstraintViolationMapper → validation errors (400)
###   - CatchAllExceptionMapper  → unhandled errors (500)
### ===========================================

@host = http://localhost:8080
@app = error-handling-demo

### ===========================================
### HAPPY PATH: Erfolgreiche Requests
### ===========================================

### Alle Produkte auflisten (5 Beispiel-Produkte)
GET {{host}}/{{app}}/api/products
Accept: application/json

### Einzelnes Produkt abrufen
GET {{host}}/{{app}}/api/products/1
Accept: application/json

### Neues Produkt anlegen — 201 Created
POST {{host}}/{{app}}/api/products
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Ergonomic Mouse",
  "price": 49.99,
  "category": "Peripherie"
}

### Produkt aktualisieren — 200 OK
PUT {{host}}/{{app}}/api/products/1
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Premium Mechanical Keyboard",
  "price": 129.99,
  "category": "Peripherie"
}

### Produkt löschen — 204 No Content
DELETE {{host}}/{{app}}/api/products/5

### ===========================================
### 404: ProductNotFoundException
### → ServiceExceptionMapper liefert JSON ErrorResponse
### ===========================================

### Produkt nicht vorhanden — 404 mit JSON Body
GET {{host}}/{{app}}/api/products/999
Accept: application/json

### Update auf nicht existierendes Produkt — 404
PUT {{host}}/{{app}}/api/products/999
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Ghost Product",
  "price": 10.00,
  "category": "Books"
}

### Delete auf nicht existierendes Produkt — 404
DELETE {{host}}/{{app}}/api/products/999

### ===========================================
### 409: DuplicateProductException
### → ServiceExceptionMapper liefert Conflict
### ===========================================

### Doppeltes Produkt anlegen — 409 Conflict
### ("Mechanical Keyboard" existiert bereits)
POST {{host}}/{{app}}/api/products
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Mechanical Keyboard",
  "price": 79.99,
  "category": "Peripherie"
}

### ===========================================
### 400: ConstraintViolationException
### → ConstraintViolationMapper liefert Feldliste
### ===========================================

### Leerer Name — @NotBlank verletzt
POST {{host}}/{{app}}/api/products
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "",
  "price": 29.99,
  "category": "Electronics"
}

### Negativer Preis — @Positive verletzt
POST {{host}}/{{app}}/api/products
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Bad Product",
  "price": -10.00,
  "category": "Software"
}

### Fehlender Preis (null) — @NotNull verletzt
POST {{host}}/{{app}}/api/products
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "No Price Product",
  "category": "Books"
}

### Mehrere Fehler gleichzeitig — alle Violations in einer Response
POST {{host}}/{{app}}/api/products
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "",
  "price": -5.00,
  "category": ""
}

### Name zu lang (>100 Zeichen) — @Size verletzt
POST {{host}}/{{app}}/api/products
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAA",
  "price": 10.00,
  "category": "Books"
}

### ===========================================
### Vergleich: Error Response Formate
### ===========================================

### ServiceException → ErrorResponse { status, title, detail, timestamp }
### Erwartet:
### {
###   "status": 404,
###   "title": "Not Found",
###   "detail": "Product with id 999 not found",
###   "timestamp": "2026-04-01T..."
### }
GET {{host}}/{{app}}/api/products/999
Accept: application/json

### ConstraintViolation → { status, title, violations: [ { field, message } ] }
### Erwartet:
### {
###   "status": 400,
###   "title": "Validation Error",
###   "violations": [
###     { "field": "name", "message": "Name darf nicht leer sein" },
###     { "field": "price", "message": "Preis muss positiv sein" }
###   ]
### }
POST {{host}}/{{app}}/api/products
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "",
  "price": -1,
  "category": ""
}
